text: The voiced palatal lateral nasal is a type of consonant. The letter for this sound in the International Phonetic Alphabet is (ʎn). The X-SAMPA symbol for this sound is `YN/`. and this sound is similar to an affricate but it is not used in English. and this sound (õ) is the letter oang. == Sounds == Sounds like the voiced palatal lateral nasal: * w * v * q == Related pages == Category:Consonants
title: Voiced palatal lateral nasal
